                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2593: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The President of the Technical Board</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stevens</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-30T09:00:00+08:26">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 30, 1922—9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Chinese Government should be strongly urged to order at once the suspension of
                    agreement just made between the South Manchuria and the Chinese Eastern Railways
                    regarding tariff rates. Japanese interests by this agreement obtain the control
                    and marketing of the entire North Manchuria soya bean crop. This is detrimental
                    to the Chinese Eastern Railway and, what is still worse, completely violates the
                    policy of the “open door” as accepted at the Washington Conference. There is no
                    time to lose as the agreement is announced as effective tomorrow. Agreement to
                    advance large sum in cash to Chinese Eastern Railway July 1 accomplished this
                    arrangement. Technical Board will give widest press publicity to this affair
                    unless proceedings are terminated.</p>
                <p>Tokyo [and Peking?] informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stevens</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
